parameters: ...\n< Serena >

...It's so deserted. I've never seen a
brothel this quiet before.\n< Serena >

I was utterly sick of the noise in this
place, but now that it's gone, it feels
strangely odd...\n< Serena >

Who's there? The shop is... wait, isn't
that Ginny?! You bastard! Where the hell
have you been wandering off to!?\n< Deacon >
Deacon. You're safe, then.\n< Serena >

A lot has happened... and I've only just
managed to return. But this is...\n< Serena >

Yeah. You must've heard too. The madam,
she got killed.\n< Deacon >

She had her share of grudges against her
from all over... but to be killed like
that...\n< Deacon >
Did you see it happen? What occurred?\n< Serena >

I didn't see the moment she was killed.
Not just me, nobody did.\n< Deacon >

We were all just doing our jobs as
usual. Then it got to closing time, and
the madam wasn't coming out of her room,
see?\n< Deacon >

Thought it was odd, so I opened the door
and... heh. Blood and flesh were
splattered all over the room... looked
like a stew that had been thoroughly
stirred.\n< Deacon >
That is...\n< Serena >

A gruesome way to be killed... Didn't
anyone notice anything?\n< Serena >

At least I didn't notice anything. The
other whores ran off right away.\n< Deacon >

I ran off too. If the city guards found
us, they'd hang us without a second
thought, treating us as the culprits.\n< Deacon >

Then why are you here now? The city
guards are still searching for the
murderer.\n< Serena >
Lord Ganelon has got my back.\n< Deacon >

Lord Ganelon has got my back. You too,
right? Being here means...\n< Deacon >

Heh, "I'll protect you from the city
guards, so get the brothel up and
running again," he says. Makes me so
grateful I could cry... Bullshit.\n< Deacon >
...\n< Serena >

Planning to make our place a branch or
something... Just when the competition's
been crushed. They should've just kept
to themselves in the depths of the
slums.\n< Deacon >

Anyway, we're reopening the brothel.
Just the second floor though.\n< Deacon >

Ah—busy, busy. Gotta greet people,
arrange for staff, restarting a business
is...\n< Deacon >
Ah...\n< Serena >
...\n< Serena >
It's the hall door.\n< Serena >
I doubt we'll pass through here again...\n< Serena >
売春状況
２０～２９：通常売春
